content:
Giving users access to quick text lets them insert predefined messages in their emails, chats, events, tasks, Knowledge articles, and more. Service agents can respond to customers and update cases quickly and easily. Sales reps can work with their contacts, accounts, and opportunities more efficiently.

Available in: Group, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions (Salesforce Classic), Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions (Lightning Experience)

To set up quick text: Customize Application
To view quick text messages: Read on quick text
To create, edit, and delete quick text messages: Create, Edit, and Delete on quick text

Use a permission set or update profiles to give users access to the Quick Text object.

Users need:
Read permission to view and insert quick text messages
Create, Edit, and Delete permission to create and manage quick text messages

From the App Launcher, select Quick Text to open the quick text tab. Share folders with others by selecting users or groups that need access to the folder and choosing an access level: View, Edit, or Manage.

After giving users access to quick text, create standardized messages that they can use.

title: Giving Users Access to Quick Text in Service Cloud
